        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer1549362779" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer11018389789698837935">Stenger has written a number of important works (e.g., God: The Failed Hypothesis), and certainly has been described as part of the &quot;New Atheism&quot; movement himself. Here, he examines what the &quot;movement&quot; is, discusses the views of its main proponents and opponents, and looks at how society has been affected by and responded to the movement. Important is a discussion of h0w &quot;new&quot; the &quot;New Atheism&quot; really is, and how it fits in with um..., old [?] atheism. At some points, this may read a bit too tec</span>
  <span id="freeText11018389789698837935" style="display:none">Stenger has written a number of important works (e.g., God: The Failed Hypothesis), and certainly has been described as part of the "New Atheism" movement himself. Here, he examines what the "movement" is, discusses the views of its main proponents and opponents, and looks at how society has been affected by and responded to the movement. Important is a discussion of h0w "new" the "New Atheism" really is, and how it fits in with um..., old [?] atheism. At some points, this may read a bit too technical for some readers [e.g., his discussions of physics], but the book is well worth working through those bits and trying to understand what Stenger is trying to say.</span>
  <a data-text-id="11018389789698837935" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
