<div id="review_1992526410" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/1992526410" />
    <a title="André Krüger" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/54056904-andr-kr-ger"><img alt="André Krüger" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1458379501p2/54056904.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/1992526410?book_show_action=true">May 06, 2017</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="André Krüger" class="user" itemprop="url" name="André Krüger" href="/user/show/54056904-andr-kr-ger">André Krüger</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer1992526410" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer5426862616271631484">Since I stood up for science and reasoning as tools to improve us as a civilization, I have been trying to read at least 1 book per month about atheism and its morality. I can assure that this one is the best since The Demon-Haunted World: Science as a Candle in the Dark because the authors wrote so passionately about how faith in the evidence, that is, science and the scientific method, is better that faith in no evidence at all, that is, religion. I would highly recommend this book for anyone </span>
  <span id="freeText5426862616271631484" style="display:none">Since I stood up for science and reasoning as tools to improve us as a civilization, I have been trying to read at least 1 book per month about atheism and its morality. I can assure that this one is the best since The Demon-Haunted World: Science as a Candle in the Dark because the authors wrote so passionately about how faith in the evidence, that is, science and the scientific method, is better that faith in no evidence at all, that is, religion. I would highly recommend this book for anyone who wants to improve her arguments for science as a tool for improvement of the human civilization and against the dark shadows casted by religion and by the faith in pseudoscience.</span>
  <a data-text-id="5426862616271631484" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

