<div id="review_79223615" class="review nosyndicate" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/79223615" />
    <a title="Rich" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/619124-rich"><img alt="Rich" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1203560835p2/619124.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/79223615?book_show_action=true">Nov 28, 2009</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Rich" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Rich" href="/user/show/619124-rich">Rich</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/619124-rich?shelf=science">science</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/619124-rich?shelf=free-thought">free-thought</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/619124-rich?shelf=religion">religion</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer79223615" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer14728579522227192400">Although I find little to disagree with in Stenger&apos;s books (and occasional insights and perspectives lacking in other New Atheists writings), they seem haphazardly written - lacking clear structure, filled with frequent digressions, sporadic commentary on other author&apos;s works, and frequent suggestions to read his other books. He&apos;s worth reading for what he says, but not particularly elegant or inspiring in how he says it.</span>
  <span id="freeText14728579522227192400" style="display:none">Although I find little to disagree with in Stenger's books (and occasional insights and perspectives lacking in other New Atheists writings), they seem haphazardly written - lacking clear structure, filled with frequent digressions, sporadic commentary on other author's works, and frequent suggestions to read his other books. He's worth reading for what he says, but not particularly elegant or inspiring in how he says it.</span>
  <a data-text-id="14728579522227192400" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


