              <span id="reviewTextContainer157239771" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer9169679705863884286">The United States is one of the most religious “first world” nations. This is a nation where the question of God’s role in the human endeavor has become a basis of many political and social discussions. So why do books on atheism flow to the top of the reading list? It may have something to do with our continued search for reason and the growth of the atheist/agnostic movement.<br/><br/>Read more: <a target='_blank' rel='noopener nofollow' href='http://www.nyjournalofbooks.com/review/new-atheism'>http://www.nyjournalofbooks.com/revie...</a></span>
